cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with natural language processing and comprehension of procedural knowledge, which falls under the scope of this category.
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new neural comprehension model for understanding procedural knowledge, which is a subfield of AI.
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper uses visual reasoning tasks in the RecipeQA dataset, which involves understanding images and their relation to text instructions, making it relevant to this category.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new neural comprehension model that learns to dynamically update entity states, which is a machine learning task.
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with understanding text instructions and identifying key entities, which is relevant to information retrieval tasks.
